jk","Lancashire, England":"Lancashire, Engeland, Verenigd Koninkrijk","Somerset, England, United Kingdom":"Somerset, Engeland, Verenigd Koninkrijk"},"en":{"1430–1470":"1430–1470","1428–Male":"1428–Deceased","1450–1483":"1450–1483","1430":"1430","1450":"1450","1483":"1483","1470":"1470","1428":"1428","Fenworth, Somerset, England":"Somerset, England, United Kingdom","Lancashire, England":"Lancashire, England, United Kingdom","Somerset, England, United Kingdom":"Somerset, England, United Kingdom","nameMeanings":[{"name":"Fenworth","type":"LAST","attribution":"Dictionary of Family Names in Britain and Ireland © University of the West of England 2016","meanings":["English: probably a variant of   Hanworth   or   Hainsworth  ."],"variants":[{"name":"Hainsworth","meanings":["English:","(Yorkshire): habitational name from Hainworth in Keighley, Yorkshire, named from the Old English personal name <i>Hagena</i> + Old English <i>worth</i> ‘enclosure’. The intrusive <i>-s-</i> was acquired by the late 15th century, probably through false association with the Lancashire surname <i>Ainsworth</i> in 2 below.","variant of   Ainsworth   in Lancashire. Names such as <i>de Haynesworth</i> and <i>de Heynesworth</i> occur in the surrounding area in the 14th century."]},{"name":"Hanworth","meanings":["English: locative name from Cold Hanworth or Potter Hanworth (both Lincs) or Hanworth (Norfolk). The early bearers can be difficult to distinguish from those for   Hainsworth  ."]}]},{"name":"Elizabeth","type":"FIRST","attribution":"Dictionary of First Names © Patrick Hanks and Flavia Hodges 1990, 2003, 2006.","meanings":["The usual spelling of   Elisabeth   in English. It is recorded in the medieval period, but was made popular by being borne by  Queen Elizabeth I  of England (  1533–1603 ). In the 20th century it again became extremely fashionable, partly because it was the name of  Elizabeth Bowes-Lyon  (  1900–2002 ), who in  1936  became Queen Elizabeth as the wife of King George VI, and after his death in  1952  achieved great public affection as Queen Mother for nearly half a century. Even more influentially, it is the name of her daughter  Queen Elizabeth II  (  b. 1926 )."],"variants":[{"name":"Elisabeth","meanings":["The spelling of   Elizabeth   used in the Authorized Version of the New Testament, and in most modern European languages. This was the name of the mother of John the Baptist (Luke 1:60). Etymologically, the name means ‘God is my oath’, and is therefore identical with <i>Elisheba</i>, the name of the wife of Aaron according to the genealogy at Exodus 6:23. The final element seems to have been altered by association with Hebrew <i>shabbāth</i> ‘Sabbath’."]}]}],"lifeSummary":"Elizabeth Fenworth Lady was born in 1430, in Somerset, England, United Kingdom. She had at least 1 son with Robert Gibbs. She died in 1470, in Lancashire, England, United Kingdom, at the age of 40."},"et":{"1430–1470":"1430–1470","1428–Male":"1428–Surnud","1450–1483":"1450–1483","1430":"1430","1450":"1450","1483":"1483","1470":"1470","1428":"1428","Fenworth, Somerset, England":"Somerset, Inglismaa, United Kingdom","Lancashire, England":"Lancashire, Inglismaa, United Kingdom","Somerset, England, United Kingdom":"Somerset, Inglismaa, United Kingdom"},"fi":{"1430–1470":"1430–1470","1428–Male":"1428–Kuollut","1450–1483":"1450–1483","1430":"1430","1450":"1450","1483":"1483","1470":"1470","1428":"1428","Fenworth, Somerset, England":"Somerset, Englanti, Yhdistynyt kuningaskunta","Lancashire, England":"Lancashire, Englanti, Yhdistynyt kuningaskunta","Somerset, England, United Kingdom":"Somerset, Englanti, Yhdistynyt kuningaskunta"},"fr":{"1430–1470":"1430–1470","1428–Male":"1428–Décédé","1450–1483":"1450–1483","1430":"1430","1450":"1450","1483":"1483","1470":"1470","1428":"1428","Fenworth, Somerset, England":"Somerset, Angleterre, Royaume-Uni","Lancashire, England":"Lancashire, Angleterre, Royaume-Uni","Somerset, England, United Kingdom":"Somerset, Angleterre, Royaume